Bayer Expects Japan Sales to Grow Average 6% a Year Until 2015

-- B y   K a n o k o   M a t s u y a m a
-- 
2011-10-05T02:15:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/bayer-expects-japan-sales-to-grow-average-6-a-year-until-2015.html
Bayer AG (BAYN)  said it expects sales in
 Japan  to grow an average 6 percent every year until 2015. Annual
sales will increase to 2.4 billion euros by then, compared with
2 billion euros in 2010, according to a statement distributed
today at a briefing in  Tokyo .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kanoko Matsuyama in Tokyo at 
 kmatsuyama2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kyung Bok Cho at 
 kcho7@bloomberg.net  